7. Event listing for logged in user
- After login, user should see all events in card or table format
- Show:
  - event name
  - date
  - time
  - max participants
  - current participant count
  - available seats
  - participant names
- If the logged in user is already registered for that event, show:
  - "Already registered"
  and disable the join button
- If event is full, show:
  - "Event Full"
  and disable the join button
- Otherwise show a "Participate" button

8. Participation rules
- A user can register for an event only once
- When a new registration happens, available seats must decrease
- Do not allow more than 10 participants per event

9. Admin dashboard
- Admin can see:
  - list of all users
  - list of all events
  - event date and time
  - max seats
  - occupied seats
  - available seats
  - participants per event

10. Pages required
- Home page
- Register page
- Login page
- User dashboard
- Admin dashboard

11. Database design
Use SQLite and create tables automatically on startup:
- users
  - id
  - full_name
  - email
  - password
  - college
  - role
  - created_at
- events
  - id
  - title
  - event_date
  - event_time
  - max_participants
- registrations
  - id
  - user_id
  - event_id
  - created_at
- Add unique constraint on user_id + event_id to prevent duplicate participation

